# Sample InsituCache calibration trace.
# Format: port,rw,addr,size,delay   (see ../TRACE_SPEC.md)
#   port 0..3 = Spatz VLSU (through coalescer), port 4 = Snitch scalar bypass
#   rw: R=read W=write ; addr: hex 0x.. or decimal byte addr ; size bytes (0=word) ; delay = idle cyc before issue
#
# --- cold misses to 4 distinct lines on port 0 (64B line stride) ---
0,R,0x80000000,4,0
0,R,0x80000040,4,0
0,R,0x80000080,4,0
0,R,0x800000C0,4,0
# --- warm re-reads of the same 4 lines (should now hit) ---
0,R,0x80000000,4,0
0,R,0x80000040,4,0
# --- a write then read-back to the same word (write-allocate path) ---
0,W,0x80000100,4,0
0,R,0x80000100,4,2
# --- concurrent traffic on a second VLSU port, paced ---
1,R,0x80000200,4,0
1,R,0x80000240,4,4
1,R,0x80000280,4,4
# --- scalar bypass port issues two reads ---
4,R,0x80000300,4,0
4,R,0x80000340,4,8
